title: China’s quest for human genetic data spurs fears of a DNA arms race
description: China offered multiple countries help with covid-19 testing during the pandemic. The payoff for Beijing included access to the DNA of millions of people.

title: China’s growing influence, explained
description: Beijing is also extending its presence and power globally. Read key findings from The Post’s reporting on China’s growing influence and ambitions.

title: State and Justice Dept. contractor charged with spying for Ethiopia
description: A Maryland man of Ethiopian descent, Abraham Teklu Lemma, is accused of passing on classified national defense information about a region where soldiers battled rebels

title: The U.S. wants Saudi-Israel normalization. Others aren’t so sure.
description: President Biden is preparing the field for a diplomatic triumph for the Israeli prime minister: the normalization of ties between Israel and Saudi Arabia.

title: South America, particularly Brazil, will experience a scorching end to winter
description: Record-breaking heat is possible as soon as Thursday afternoon, with the worst of this round to come from about Friday to Tuesday.

title: Poland to stop sending weapons to Ukraine over grain fight
description: Russia’s attacks on Ukraine’s agriculture sector have split Kyiv and Warsaw, as Polish Prime Minister Mateusz Morawiecki looks to protect his country’s farmers.

title: Canada reduces diplomatic staff in India, citing threats as rift deepens
description: Indian company BLS International said visa services for Canadians were suspended. Canada’s High Comission said it will “adjust staff presence” in India.

title: Russia-Ukraine war live updates: Zelensky to hit White House, Congress and Pentagon on whirlwind day
description: President Volodymyr Zelensky’s schedule includes talks with congressional leaders and Pentagon officials, as well as meetings with President Biden.

title: Tensions ‘beginning to boil’ in Gaza as fears of new conflict mount
description: Neither Israel nor Hamas wants a military confrontation, security experts said, but both have hard-liners to appease. In Gaza, the next war never feels far off.

title: U.S. domestic battle on abortion clouds Biden’s global push
description: As the president reaches out to the Global South, PEPFAR, a widely praised initiative to fight AIDS in poorer nations, faces a reauthorization fight.

title: Amid new border strains, Biden extends legal status to 470,000 Venezuelans
description: Biden administration officials told reporters that Venezuelans who entered the United States by July 31 would be eligible for temporary protected status
